      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must directly correspond to the clinical decision threshold quantities specified in the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation QoIs include normalized hemolysis index and bulk-averaged shear stress but do not capture localized high-shear zones that govern clinical hemolysis thresholds. Partial relevance warrants achieved level 2."
